in Miami Beach, Florida.

02:50.303 --> 02:52.179
Versace was a fashion icon.

02:52.190 --> 02:54.155
(VOLUME INCREASES):
His empire spanned the worlds

02:54.165 --> 02:56.157
of the famous and perhaps the infamous.

02:56.167 --> 02:57.525
Investigators are probing

02:57.535 --> 03:00.095
whether he was targeted
by organized crime

03:00.105 --> 03:02.130
or perhaps a serial killer.

03:02.140 --> 03:04.432
Our CBS News coverage of the death of

03:04.442 --> 03:06.976
the designer begins
at the scene of the crime,

03:06.986 --> 03:09.104
with CBS News correspondent Jim Axelrod.

03:09.114 --> 03:12.240
AXELROD: The blood on the steps of
the most famous house in Miami Beach

03:12.250 --> 03:14.376
belonged to one of
its most famous residents,

03:14.386 --> 03:17.412
designer Gianni Versace,
murdered this morning.

03:17.422 --> 03:20.181
I saw Gianni Versace laying face down

03:20.191 --> 03:24.152
on his steps with his head blown
off, with his face shot off.

03:24.162 --> 03:26.121
- (LOUD POP)
- Oh! (LAUGHS)

03:26.131 --> 03:28.089
MAN: execution-style,
shot in the head

03:28.099 --> 03:29.457
right on his steps...

03:29.467 --> 03:33.061
NEWSWOMAN (ON TV): The death
of this famous idol and icon

03:33.071 --> 03:35.371
reverberates greatly
through this small community

03:35.381 --> 03:39.034
where Versace was a popular presence.

03:39.044 --> 03:40.376
Police are now confirming

03:40.386 --> 03:44.139
the suspect is a young man,
Andrew Cunanan.

03:44.149 --> 03:47.142
An eyewitness describes
Cunanan approached Versace

03:47.152 --> 03:49.344
- and fired two shots...
- Oh, my God.

03:49.354 --> 03:51.120
at point blank range.

03:51.130 --> 03:53.415
Mr. Versace collapsed immediately.

03:53.425 --> 03:56.225
- The suspect then...
- Oh, my God.

03:56.235 --> 03:59.421
