(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

10:16.593 --> 10:19.319
(KEYS JINGLING)

10:19.329 --> 10:21.588
(JINGLING ECHOES)

10:45.313 --> 10:47.213
(CAR ENGINE STARTS)

10:47.223 --> 10:49.215
(ON RADIO): Rumors swirled
that it was perhaps

10:49.225 --> 10:50.617
a hit by the Italian Mafia.

10:50.627 --> 10:52.418
- (LAUGHS)
- This is all too common

10:52.428 --> 10:54.385
whenever something unexpected
happens in America,

10:54.396 --> 10:56.314
or anywhere else in the world,
that involves

10:56.324 --> 10:58.491
an influential Italian
such as Gianni Versace.

10:58.501 --> 11:00.493
There's rampant speculation

11:00.503 --> 11:03.329
that the so-called Black Hand
of the Mob is involved.

11:03.339 --> 11:05.365
- But right now, they're watching...
- Oh, shit.

11:05.375 --> 11:07.592
to see what U.S. authorities
are trying to do

11:07.602 --> 11:09.402
to catch their prime suspect.

11:09.412 --> 11:11.471
Versace was the genius behind...

11:13.508 --> 11:16.242
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

11:19.381 --> 11:21.547
Patience. Sit tight.

11:33.395 --> 11:36.229
(MUTTERS QUIETLY)

11:36.239 --> 11:37.597
Shit!

11:43.438 --> 11:44.846
You look a little lost.

11:45.440 --> 11:47.732
Uh, yes, I am.

11:47.742 --> 11:50.243
I'm not from around here.

11:50.253 --> 11:53.413
There seems to be an awful lot
of traffic on these causeways.

11:53.423 --> 11:56.408
Do you know if these other roads up here

11:56.418 --> 11:58.343
are a little less congested?

11:58.353 --> 11:59.678
Nah, there are police checkpoints

11:59.688 --> 12:01.621
on every road off the island.

12:01.631 --> 12:03.715
Police checkpoints?

12:03.725 --> 12:06.641
They're looking for the man
who shot Versace.

12:07.629 --> 12:09.654
Oh, yeah, yeah.

12:09.664 --> 12:11.690
Andrew Cunanan.

12:11.700 --> 12:14.409
It's terrible. I-I hope they catch him.

12:15.570 --> 12:17.562
What's your name, young man?

12:17.572 --> 12:21.441
Kurt. Kurt DeMars.

12:21.451 --> 12:23.276
You've been very helpful.

12:23.286 --> 12:25.784
I'll be sure to allow extra time.

12:26.648 --> 12:28.640
Thank you, sir.

12:28.650 --> 12:31.317
(ENGINE STARTS)

12:43.665 --> 12:45.631
(KEYS JINGLE)

12:47.736 --> 12:51.529
(SCREAMS)

12:51.539 --> 12:53.406
NEWSWOMAN (ON TV): Andrew Cunanan,

12:53.416 --> 12:55.575
the man who murdered
fashion designer Gianni Versace

12:55.585 --> 12:57.577
yesterday in Miami,
has now become the subject

12:57.587 --> 13:00.480
of one of the FBI's
largest manhunts of all time.

13:00.490 --> 13:02.248
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

13:02.258 --> 13:04.283
But Cunanan's beginnings were small.

13:19.960 --> 13:22.175
Have you killed my son?

13:23.371 --> 13:25.338
♪ ♪

13:29.377 --> 13:31.577
(PANTING SOFTLY)

13:46.394 --> 13:48.361
♪ ♪

13:55.403 --> 13:58.237
NEWSMAN (ON TV):
Regarding Andrew Cunanan,

13:58.247 --> 14:01.507
the situation out here
has escalated as word spreads

14:01.517 --> 14:05.344
that one of National
City's own is responsible

14:05.354 --> 14:07.513
or accused of murdering Gianni Versace

14:07.523 --> 14:10.416
and four other men in brutal killings

14:10.426 --> 14:12.385
that have captivated national attention.

14:12.395 --> 14:14.353
NEWSWOMAN: I'm standing outside the home

14:14.363 --> 14:18.191
of Mary Anne Cunanan, here
in National City, California.

14:18.201 --> 14:21.327
FBI agents are questioning her
for information

14:21.337 --> 14:23.563
about her son
Andrew Cunanan's whereabouts.

14:23.573 --> 14:27.400
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

14:27.410 --> 14:29.327
Tell us, Mary Anne. Where is he?

14:29.337 --> 14:30.595
Why did he do it?

14:30.605 --> 14:33.506
(CLAMORING CONTINUES)

14:33.516 --> 14:36.409
- Back up.
- Look, look, look.

14:36.419 --> 14:38.544
MAN: You think he's in Miami?

14:44.719 --> 14:47.345
(DISTORTED VOICES ECHOING)

14:47.355 --> 14:49.355
(CLAMORING CONTINUES)

14:50.725 --> 14:52.617
All right.

14:52.627 --> 14:54.594
(REPORTERS CLAMORING ON TV)

15:02.503 --> 15:05.137
<i>(POUNDING ON DOOR)</i>

15:05.147 --> 15:06.264
<i>(DOOR OPENS)</i>

15:06.274 --> 15:08.207
You lied to us, Ronnie.

15:08.217 --> 15:10.927
- I didn't lie to you.
- We asked if you knew Andrew.

15:10.938 --> 15:13.654
You said no, but Andrew stayed
here <i> and</i> you were friends.

15:13.665 --> 15:15.170
He told me his name was Kurt.

15:15.181 --> 15:17.542
I only this minute
saw his face on the news.

15:17.553 --> 15:19.904
- I was just about to call you guys.
- All right, let's go.

15:19.915 --> 15:21.450
Come on. Take him.

15:23.725 --> 15:25.717
And we weren't friends.

15:25.727 --> 15:28.194
LORI: <i> He was hiding here for two months.</i>

15:28.204 --> 15:30.331
Hiding? He wasn't hiding.

15:30.342 --> 15:31.497
So what was he doing?

15:31.507 --> 15:34.267
- He was partying.
- Where?

15:34.277 --> 15:35.727
Twist?

15:35.737 --> 15:37.595
Warsaw Ballroom?

15:37.605 --> 15:40.465
Oh, you were looking for him,
weren't you?

15:40.475 --> 15:41.935
The only lez on the force?

15:41.946 --> 15:43.738
Where's Cunanan now?

15:44.044 --> 15:46.094
But the other cops, yeah,

15:46.105 --> 15:49.574
they weren't searching so
hard, were they? Why is that?

15:49.584 --> 15:51.576
Because he killed
a bunch of nobody gays?

15:51.586 --> 15:53.678
Hey, we got over 400 agents
and detectives

15:53.688 --> 15:55.521
searching for him right now.

15:55.531 --> 15:58.557
Well, sure, yeah, now...
that he killed a celebrity.

15:58.567 --> 16:01.037
- You're an accessory to murder.
- Oh, please.

16:01.047 --> 16:03.161
Couldn't find a gay,
so now you're gonna blame a gay?

16:03.172 --> 16:05.756
Whoa, whoa, you think this is a joke?

16:05.766 --> 16:07.536
- This a joke to you?
- Is <i> he</i> a joke to <i> you?</i>

16:07.547 --> 16:09.939
You think we don't want to catch him?

16:12.020 --> 16:14.212
So he didn't talk about Versace?

16:14.567 --> 16:15.800
Hmm?

16:17.504 --> 16:20.678
He didn't <i> stop</i> talking about Versace.

16:21.616 --> 16:23.980
Look, we all talked about him.

16:24.719 --> 16:27.186
We all imagined what it would be like

16:27.196 --> 16:29.714
to be so rich and so powerful that...

16:29.724 --> 16:32.036
it doesn't matter that you're gay.

16:32.908 --> 16:34.426
You know what the truth is?

16:34.437 --> 16:36.629
It's that you were disgusted by him

16:36.639 --> 16:39.880
long before he became disgusting.

16:40.601 --> 16:43.461
You're so used to us
lurking in the shadows,

16:43.471 --> 16:46.631
and, you know, most of us, we oblige.

16:46.641 --> 16:49.600
People like me,
we just, we-we drift away.

16:49.610 --> 16:52.537
We get sick, no-nobody cares.

16:52.547 --> 16:55.673
But Andrew was vain.

16:55.683 --> 16:58.576
He wanted you to know about his pain.

16:58.586 --> 17:02.399
He wanted you to hear. He wanted you...

17:03.491 --> 17:07.598
he wanted you to know
about being born a lie.

17:11.499 --> 17:14.867
Andrew is not hiding.

17:16.704 --> 17:19.372
He's trying to be seen.

17:20.641 --> 17:23.476
(SQUAWKING)

17:27.582 --> 17:29.548
(MEN TALKING QUIETLY)

17:40.461 --> 17:42.428
♪ ♪

18:10.324 --> 18:12.291
♪ ♪

18:23.337 --> 18:25.671
WOMAN (IN DISTANCE):
Guillermo, are you there?

18:27.762 --> 18:29.662
Guillermo?

18:35.831 --> 18:38.699
Didn't know you were
taking her out today.

18:40.514 --> 18:42.314
Ahoy?

18:53.634 --> 18:55.468
Guillermo?

18:58.539 --> 19:00.465
(QUIET CLICK)

19:00.475 --> 19:02.441
(BOAT CREAKING)

19:18.659 --> 19:20.687
WOMAN (QUIETLY): Honey.

19:21.596 --> 19:24.296
- Honey, call the cops.
- (FOOTSTEPS ABOVE)

19:26.501 --> 19:28.467
♪ ♪

19:43.351 --> 19:44.542
<i>(DOOR CLOSES)</i>

19:44.552 --> 19:49.321
(ON TV): The question remains: did
Andrew Cunanan know Gianni Versace?

19:49.331 --> 19:51.390
(TV CONTINUES QUIETLY)

20:02.370 --> 20:04.328
NEWSWOMAN: Who is Andrew Cunanan?

20:04.338 --> 20:06.631
To help us, we turn
to his closest friend,

20:06.641 --> 20:08.366
Lizzie Cote.

20:08.376 --> 20:10.701
LIZZIE: Andrew, I wrote this statement

20:10.711 --> 20:14.924
on behalf of your family and myself.

20:14.935 --> 20:17.349
These past few months,
you have been portrayed

20:17.359 --> 20:20.212
as a horrible and despicable person.

20:20.984 --> 20:24.995
But I just want you to know
that I remember

20:25.426 --> 20:30.008
and know who you really are,
and I love you, unconditionally.

20:31.065 --> 20:34.892
The Andrew Cunanan that I know
is not a violent person.

20:35.403 --> 20:38.729
I know that the most important
thing to you in the world

20:38.739 --> 20:41.465
is what others think of you.

20:41.475 --> 20:44.958
You still have a chance
to show the entire world

20:45.513 --> 20:49.774
the side of you that I
and your godchildren know.

20:49.784 --> 20:53.909
The time has come
for this to end, peacefully.

21:00.660 --> 21:02.922
NEWSMAN: <i>Jeff Trail
was brutally murdered</i>

21:02.933 --> 21:04.486
<i>in David Madson's apartment.</i>

21:04.496 --> 21:06.454
<i>Madson then goes on the run</i>

21:06.464 --> 21:09.265
<i>with the now notorious killer
of Versace, Andrew Cunanan.</i>

21:10.475 --> 21:11.867
<i>What was the connection, though,</i>

21:11.877 --> 21:13.513
<i>between Cunanan and Madson?</i>

21:13.523 --> 21:14.808
<i>Were they lovers?</i>

21:14.819 --> 21:17.011
<i>What did those men do
on the road together?</i>

21:17.022 --> 21:19.886
<i>We looked deeper at this
dark and disturbing mystery</i>

21:19.897 --> 21:21.322
<i>of their days on the road.</i>

21:21.756 --> 21:24.910
Welcome back. With us now from
his home is Mr. Howard Madson.

21:24.921 --> 21:26.917
Howard, thank you so much
for being here.

21:26.928 --> 21:29.019
Mr. Madson, do you have any idea at all

21:29.030 --> 21:31.716
what happened
after the murder of Jeff Trail?

21:31.727 --> 21:33.412
My son is innocent.

21:33.422 --> 21:35.426
He's a victim of a brutal murder.

21:35.886 --> 21:38.919
And to have a cloud of suspicion
hanging over him,

21:38.929 --> 21:40.342
it's devastating.

21:40.352 --> 21:42.709
That's why I want the killer
to give himself up

21:42.719 --> 21:44.900
and tell the world
David did nothing wrong.

21:44.910 --> 21:48.061
The police won't... (ON NEARBY
TV): it's destroying us.

21:48.071 --> 21:49.936
NEWSMAN: But, sir,
if David's truly innocent,

21:49.947 --> 21:51.639
why didn't he run away?

21:51.650 --> 21:52.745
(TURNS OFF TV)

21:52.756 --> 21:55.416
(ON DISTANT TV): Why did
he leave with Mr. Cunanan?

21:55.427 --> 21:56.870
HOWARD: Because...

21:57.213 --> 21:59.393
because he didn't know
evil like this could exist.

22:00.739 --> 22:02.685
He must have...

22:02.695 --> 22:05.988
David must have thought
he could... stop him.

22:05.998 --> 22:08.605
But he didn't know how,
so he went with him.

22:08.616 --> 22:10.601
My son's a good man.

22:10.935 --> 22:12.961
My son <i> was</i> a good man.

22:12.972 --> 22:15.097
(TV CLICKS OFF)

22:15.107 --> 22:18.834
(LIVELY LATIN MUSIC PLAYING IN DISTANCE)

22:18.844 --> 22:20.903
(HORNS HONKING IN DISTANCE)

22:29.208 --> 22:32.874
MAN (ON TV): I'd like to
introduce you to item 11-06281,

22:32.884 --> 22:35.143
an immaculate crystal recreation

22:35.153 --> 22:37.953
of a narrow-necked Ming dynasty vase.

22:37.963 --> 22:40.022
(TV CONTINUES QUIETLY)

22:43.895 --> 22:45.887
Well, yes, and also no.

22:45.898 --> 22:50.114
And if you're already enticed,
pick up your phone and call...

22:57.208 --> 22:59.008
(SIGHS)

23:04.115 --> 23:06.082
♪ ♪

23:14.758 --> 23:17.351
MAN (ON TV): Pick up the phone,
give us a call.

23:17.361 --> 23:19.294
You know you want this
to decorate your home.

23:19.304 --> 23:22.764
- Ladies, thank you so much.
- (COUGHING)

23:26.570 --> 23:27.803
(SPITTING)

23:30.574 --> 23:32.399
(GROANS)

23:32.409 --> 23:34.368
TERRY: Now, Marilyn,
you said to me earlier

23:34.378 --> 23:35.669
that you consider this perfume

23:35.679 --> 23:38.347
to be one of your
finest creations to date.

23:38.357 --> 23:41.583
MARILYN: Terry, my most personal. It is.

23:41.593 --> 23:43.485
TERRY: Now, what does that mean exactly,

23:43.495 --> 23:45.687
when you say a fragrance is "personal"?

23:45.697 --> 23:47.940
MARILYN: Well, I...

23:47.958 --> 23:51.492
I always wanted
to make a perfume for my mother.

23:51.503 --> 23:52.627
(TERI CHUCKLES)

23:52.637 --> 23:54.563
Just not in honor of her...

23:54.573 --> 23:56.440
- Okay.
- but an actual gift

23:56.451 --> 24:00.411
that I would give her
if I could go back in time.

24:00.429 --> 24:05.324
You see, Terry, my father died
when I was just 11 years old.

24:05.550 --> 24:07.476
- That's so sad. I didn't know.
- Oh, please.

24:07.486 --> 24:09.611
Well, he-he was a very kind man,

24:09.621 --> 24:13.281
and, um, he was a wonderful storyteller.

24:13.291 --> 24:15.517
He would invent all kinds of stories

24:15.527 --> 24:17.877
to entertain my friends
when they would come round.

24:17.888 --> 24:20.981
Not soppy stories for girls, but...

24:20.992 --> 24:24.052
things that were scary
and thrilling and...

24:24.603 --> 24:28.430
W-We... we loved him very much.

24:28.440 --> 24:31.566
And suddenly my father
was taken from us.

24:32.954 --> 24:35.869
Life was never the same without him.

24:36.615 --> 24:40.509
My mother had to work long hours
just to make ends meet.

24:40.519 --> 24:43.180
And even though I was young...

24:43.190 --> 24:45.480
I had to get a job.

24:45.490 --> 24:50.385
And my mother always felt
terribly guilty about that.

24:50.403 --> 24:54.731
Of course, she had no extra
money for luxuries of any kind.

24:56.088 --> 24:57.550
So...

24:59.537 --> 25:03.313
I imagine going back in time...

25:04.668 --> 25:06.701
and telling her...

25:08.833 --> 25:12.408
"Here's something that I made for you."

25:13.610 --> 25:18.413
"The kind of perfume
my father would have given you"

25:18.423 --> 25:20.923
"for your birthday."

25:23.424 --> 25:27.307
"As a way of saying
how special you are."

25:28.625 --> 25:31.626
TERRY: Marilyn, what a beautiful story.

25:31.636 --> 25:34.329
- MARILYN: Oh, thank you.
- For a beautiful perfume.

25:34.339 --> 25:36.398
And to our wonderful home shoppers...

25:44.827 --> 25:46.556
- (BIRDS CHIRPING)
- (ROOSTER CROWING)

25:46.566 --> 25:48.643
(DOGS BARKING IN DISTANCE)

25:50.342 --> 25:52.739
<i>Oi!</i> Modesto!

25:52.749 --> 25:55.060
- MODESTO: Hmm?
- You have a call.

25:55.070 --> 25:57.352
Another interview request?

25:57.362 --> 25:59.910
How much do you think
I should charge this time?

26:00.431 --> 26:03.014
It's... it's Andrew.

26:07.422 --> 26:08.702
MODESTO: Andrew?

26:09.366 --> 26:11.633
- Andrew?
- (SOBBING, SNORTING)

26:11.643 --> 26:13.678
- Don't cry.
- (SOBBING CONTINUES)

26:13.689 --> 26:15.561
Please don't cry.

26:15.572 --> 26:17.248
Men don't cry, remember?

26:17.259 --> 26:18.650
Dad, I'm in trouble.

26:19.483 --> 26:21.295
And I need help.

26:21.306 --> 26:23.107
I need help. I need you to come get me.

26:23.934 --> 26:25.694
I'll fly over right away.

26:26.383 --> 26:29.409
There might still be some
outstanding charges against me,

26:29.419 --> 26:31.334
but... but so what? Huh?

26:31.345 --> 26:33.795
As soon as I put this phone down,

26:34.466 --> 26:36.491
I'll be on my way.

26:36.501 --> 26:39.007
- Where are you?
- I'm still in Miami.

26:39.829 --> 26:42.296
- Okay.
- I'm in a houseboat.

26:42.307 --> 26:44.379
On 54th Street and...

26:44.389 --> 26:47.369
- Collins Avenue.
- I'll be there.

26:47.471 --> 26:49.196
24 hours.

26:49.673 --> 26:51.344
I'm coming. Do you hear me?

26:51.354 --> 26:54.146
I will find you, and I will hug you.

26:54.929 --> 26:56.725
And I will hold you in my arms.

26:57.748 --> 26:58.998
Like I used to.

27:00.431 --> 27:02.131
And it will all be okay.

27:03.420 --> 27:04.444
You promise?

27:04.455 --> 27:05.787
I promise!

27:06.560 --> 27:09.086
Now, pack some clothes,

27:09.096 --> 27:12.294
stay out of sight, and wait for me.

27:12.304 --> 27:14.555
You be ready to leave
as soon as I arrive.

27:14.565 --> 27:16.436
(BEEP) AUTOMATED VOICE: Your time is up.

27:16.447 --> 27:19.019
- Please deposit 25 cents for 4 minutes.
- I'm out of time.

27:19.030 --> 27:21.559
MODESTO: I'll be there soon.
Do you hear me?

27:21.570 --> 27:24.596
- (BEEP)
- Andrew? I'll be there soon.

27:24.607 --> 27:26.374
(LINE CLICKS)

27:30.480 --> 27:32.347
(LINE BEEPING)

27:41.458 --> 27:44.559
(PIANO PLAYING "THE MAN I LOVE")

28:01.445 --> 28:03.411
(PIANO MUSIC CONTINUES)

28:15.425 --> 28:18.493
(PIANO MUSIC CONTINUES)

28:34.611 --> 28:36.578
(SIGHS)

28:45.890 --> 28:48.556
NEWSMAN (ON TV): Miami police
have stated that their best hope

28:48.566 --> 28:51.326
for catching Cunanan may be
that someone will spot him.

28:51.336 --> 28:53.171
And the FBI is using
their mighty manpower

28:53.182 --> 28:54.588
to check train and airplane records

28:54.598 --> 28:56.498
looking for single, young, Caucasian men

28:56.508 --> 28:58.433
who purchased one-way tickets with cash

28:58.443 --> 29:00.735
within 12 hours of
Versace's murder. Miami...

29:16.753 --> 29:19.483
NEWSMAN: Do you believe
your son is innocent?

29:19.987 --> 29:22.319
MODESTO: Of course he's innocent.

29:23.008 --> 29:27.915
My son is not, and has
never been, a homosexual.

29:27.925 --> 29:29.627
That is a slur.

29:29.637 --> 29:33.185
Maybe there were some older men
who manipulated him.

29:33.637 --> 29:35.283
NEWSMAN: And the murders?

29:35.293 --> 29:37.042
MODESTO: You never saw my son?

29:37.374 --> 29:40.364
He was a... a perfect boy.

29:41.270 --> 29:44.308
The most special child I ever saw.

29:45.265 --> 29:48.650
The idea that he could be a killer

29:48.660 --> 29:50.307
makes me angry.

29:50.317 --> 29:52.053
Have you been in contact with Andrew?

29:52.063 --> 29:55.611
Yes. He phones me regularly.

29:56.399 --> 29:59.005
- Since the murders took place?
- Sure. Yes.

29:59.015 --> 30:01.621
Last night, he called me.

30:01.631 --> 30:04.241
- NEWSMAN: You know where he is?
- All I can say

30:04.251 --> 30:06.625
is that he's evaded the police again.

30:07.346 --> 30:10.605
He's far too clever for them.
He's a genius.

30:10.615 --> 30:12.574
They'll never catch him.

30:12.584 --> 30:14.801
NEWSMAN: What did you discuss?

30:14.811 --> 30:17.679
MODESTO: The movie rights
to his life story.

30:17.689 --> 30:19.385
I'm acting as the broker,

30:19.396 --> 30:21.862
calling Hollywood from here in Manila.

30:22.439 --> 30:26.004
Andrew was very particular
about the title.

30:26.014 --> 30:27.649
Can you share it?

30:29.126 --> 30:32.012
<i>A Name to Be Remembered By.</i>

30:32.868 --> 30:34.143
Andrew made me promise.

30:34.154 --> 30:37.198
That had to be the title, no other.

30:37.208 --> 30:41.162
We're in, uh, early discussions
with several studios.

30:41.638 --> 30:44.955
NEWSMAN: But you can't travel
because of the charges against you.

30:44.965 --> 30:46.784
Those charges are bogus.

30:46.794 --> 30:49.444
But that's okay. I can make the...

30:59.153 --> 31:01.674
_

31:02.471 --> 31:04.670
(BELL TOLLING)

31:04.997 --> 31:07.269
_

31:07.279 --> 31:10.047
DONATELLA: <i>My brother should be alive.</i>

31:12.284 --> 31:15.384
If everybody had done their job,
he would be alive.

31:17.151 --> 31:19.956
I heard the shot, that morning,

31:19.966 --> 31:21.016
and I knew.

31:22.294 --> 31:24.044
Before I ran out, I knew.

31:25.297 --> 31:28.108
Because my heart stopped.

31:30.302 --> 31:32.602
I'm sure your heart is broken, too.

31:34.173 --> 31:35.873
But you have each other.

31:38.638 --> 31:39.638
I had him.

31:41.046 --> 31:42.296
I only had him.

31:43.315 --> 31:46.224
What will you do now, Antonio?

31:48.582 --> 31:50.982
I'm going to stay in Lake Como.

31:51.922 --> 31:55.125
As I'm sure you know, Gianni arranged
so I can stay in one of the houses.

31:55.135 --> 31:58.195
I just want, I just want
to stay close to him.

32:02.328 --> 32:05.725
Gianni doesn't own any of the houses.

32:07.352 --> 32:08.944
I don't understand.

32:08.955 --> 32:11.133
He spent too much money.

32:11.143 --> 32:15.173
The company was forced to take
possession of all the properties.

32:15.962 --> 32:19.282
They are controlled
by the board of Versace.

32:29.120 --> 32:32.839
You should go to Lake Como
after the funeral.

32:33.232 --> 32:36.422
Take some time, relax, recover.

32:36.801 --> 32:38.768
And after that?

32:47.346 --> 32:51.148
Today is the day for saying good-bye.

32:53.185 --> 32:56.787
We start a new life, both of us.

33:01.827 --> 33:03.577
And that's it for me now?

33:04.780 --> 33:07.399
I cannot be thrown away
like a piece of trash.

33:07.409 --> 33:09.350
I loved him, Donatella.

33:10.269 --> 33:11.519
He was my life.

33:13.839 --> 33:15.739
And suddenly I don't matter?

33:17.142 --> 33:18.754
I don't have a home?

33:18.764 --> 33:21.077
I have no rights? I have nothing.

33:22.740 --> 33:24.905
As I explained to you,

33:25.884 --> 33:27.809
the houses, the finances,

33:27.819 --> 33:30.086
they are controlled by the board.

33:30.096 --> 33:32.111
You have a say.

33:33.823 --> 33:36.010
I'm sorry for your loss.

33:37.834 --> 33:39.982
I'm sorry for all of us.

33:48.273 --> 33:51.266
MAN (ON TV): <i>It's not true.
It's not possible.</i>

33:51.276 --> 33:53.844
Because, uh, you know,

33:53.854 --> 33:56.079
when you see a man, 50 years old,

33:56.089 --> 33:59.082
healthy, happy, lucky,

33:59.092 --> 34:03.119
and you, and you hear that this man...

34:03.129 --> 34:07.530
died suddenly, and we didn't know why,

34:07.541 --> 34:09.092
we didn't know the reason.

34:09.101 --> 34:12.780
NEWSMAN: Versace was referred to as
the master of glamour and glitz,

34:12.791 --> 34:14.889
and he found massive success

34:14.900 --> 34:17.033
by dressing his clothes
on the rich and beautiful.

34:17.043 --> 34:18.983
"A man in search
of the essence of beauty"

34:18.994 --> 34:21.036
is how he was described
by Princess Diana,

34:21.047 --> 34:22.991
who often wore his creations.

34:23.002 --> 34:26.632
Versace's memorial will be held
inside Milan's iconic Duomo.

34:26.643 --> 34:28.295
Those in attendance will remember.

34:28.306 --> 34:30.947
Versace's favorite quote
from a Russian author:

34:30.956 --> 34:33.342
"Beauty will save the world."

34:33.353 --> 34:36.753
All the guests, including
Princess Diana and Elton John,

34:36.763 --> 34:40.824
are now inside for the funeral
of Gianni Versace.

34:43.896 --> 34:45.862
(GRUNTS)

34:50.869 --> 34:52.835
(SOMBER ORGAN MUSIC PLAYING)

35:01.213 --> 35:03.179
(ORGAN MUSIC CONTINUES)

35:20.933 --> 35:25.160
<i>In nomine Patris et Filii
et Spiritus Sancti.</i>

35:25.170 --> 35:26.380
Amen.

35:26.398 --> 35:30.513
The loss of Gianni Versace
has been felt around the world.

35:31.479 --> 35:34.432
But let us not forget the man himself.

35:35.080 --> 35:38.245
He leaves behind a family:

35:38.917 --> 35:41.249
his older brother, Santo,

35:42.020 --> 35:44.888
his younger sister, Donatella.

35:46.200 --> 35:49.758
Their love for him was incomparable.

35:50.463 --> 35:52.342
To these people...

35:52.352 --> 35:54.575
those closest to him,

35:55.934 --> 35:57.377
his loved ones...

35:57.930 --> 36:00.304
we offer our prayers.

36:01.054 --> 36:02.558
Let us pray.

36:03.809 --> 36:05.775
(LIGHT CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)

