♪ Forever ♪

37:51.814 --> 37:53.627
WOMAN (ON TV):
<i>The Miami Police Department</i>

37:53.638 --> 37:55.876
<i>has reason to believe that
Cunanan is still in the area.</i>

37:55.887 --> 37:58.013
- We're working together with the FBI.
- MAN: Uh-huh.

37:58.023 --> 38:00.048
and doing everything we can to find him.

38:00.058 --> 38:01.530
(TV CONTINUES QUIETLY)

38:01.541 --> 38:04.093
No. I-I take care of it.

38:04.804 --> 38:06.930
No. It's no problem.

38:16.133 --> 38:18.100
(VEHICLE APPROACHES OUTSIDE)

38:20.979 --> 38:23.780
(VEHICLE DOOR OPENS)

38:23.791 --> 38:25.850
♪ ♪

38:31.857 --> 38:34.090
(KEYS JINGLING)

38:36.128 --> 38:38.094
(TV PLAYING QUIETLY)

38:54.012 --> 38:55.979
Is anybody here?

39:02.578 --> 39:04.663
I am armed.

39:18.880 --> 39:20.802
DISPATCHER (OVER RADIO):
54th Street and Collins.

39:20.813 --> 39:23.807
We have an occupied burglary.
Location is a houseboat.

39:23.817 --> 39:26.976
All units, shut down traffic
on Collins immediately.

39:26.986 --> 39:29.112
REPEAT: occupied burglary.

39:29.122 --> 39:32.015
- Location is a houseboat.
- (TIRES SCREECHING)

39:32.025 --> 39:35.819
(ALARM BLARING)

39:38.840 --> 39:40.849
NEWSMAN: <i>We're interrupting
our current program</i>

39:40.859 --> 39:43.993
to bring you a live update in
the hunt for Versace's killer.

39:44.003 --> 39:46.856
Reports are coming in that
law enforcement in Miami Beach

39:46.867 --> 39:50.066
have cordoned off a houseboat
on the Indian Creek canal

39:50.076 --> 39:51.598
and that a standoff

39:51.609 --> 39:54.037
- is currently in progress.
- (HELICOPTER APPROACHING)

39:54.047 --> 39:56.973
Law enforcement has blocked off
access on both sides

39:56.983 --> 39:58.809
- of Collins Avenue,
- (SIRENS APPROACHING)

39:58.820 --> 40:00.268
creating a perimeter.

40:00.278 --> 40:03.179
SWAT and FBI agents
are on scene, as well,

40:03.189 --> 40:06.637
to assess and assist in the situation.

40:07.060 --> 40:11.287
For more on this developing
story, we go live to Miami Beach.

40:17.514 --> 40:19.311
NEWSMAN: <i>If you're just tuning in,</i>

40:19.322 --> 40:21.285
<i>we are here on 54th and Collins Avenue,</i>

40:21.296 --> 40:23.527
<i>where we believe suspected killer.</i>

40:23.538 --> 40:25.685
<i>Andrew Cunanan has been hiding out.</i>

40:26.707 --> 40:28.573
I'm reporting live at Collins Avenue,

40:28.584 --> 40:30.709
where police have taken
extraordinary measure,

40:30.719 --> 40:33.645
shutting down the street
and blocking traffic.

40:33.655 --> 40:36.264
(ON TV): As you can see
behind me, there's much interest

40:36.275 --> 40:39.551
in a baby blue houseboat
located on the Indian Creek.

40:39.561 --> 40:42.421
- I've never seen anything quite
like this, - (HOUSE RUMBLING)

40:42.431 --> 40:44.522
as police, marine patrol, and the FBI

40:44.533 --> 40:46.707
- are all coordinating together.
- (RUMBLING CONTINUES)

40:46.718 --> 40:49.302
With this extreme show
of force, we can't help but...

40:51.273 --> 40:53.432
(PHONE RINGING)

40:53.442 --> 40:54.633
NEWSWOMAN:
the alleged Versace killer,

40:54.643 --> 40:56.468
Andrew Cunanan, is in that houseboat.

40:56.478 --> 40:59.471
OFFICER (OVER BULLHORN):
Mr. Cunanan, this is the police.

40:59.481 --> 41:02.307
- We just want to talk.
- (HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

41:02.317 --> 41:04.610
Please be calm.

41:04.620 --> 41:08.313
- I repeat, we just want to talk.
- (PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

41:08.323 --> 41:11.257
We know you're in there,
and we can help.

41:11.268 --> 41:13.624
Hold the position.
Wait for the green light.

41:13.635 --> 41:16.888
Just hold the position. Stand by.

41:17.147 --> 41:19.866
NEWSMAN: <i>I'm reporting live
from Collins Avenue,</i>

41:19.884 --> 41:22.464
where my sources say
all attempts to communicate

41:22.475 --> 41:24.771
with the fugitive seems to have failed.

41:24.781 --> 41:28.257
Snipers are in position, ready to react

41:28.268 --> 41:29.968
in the event that Mr. Cunanan

41:29.978 --> 41:32.429
makes yet another run for flight.

41:32.440 --> 41:35.007
Stay with us as we give you
comprehensive coverage

41:35.018 --> 41:37.684
of the siege at Indian Creek.

41:37.694 --> 41:39.686
♪ ♪

41:42.690 --> 41:44.590
(PANTING)

41:44.601 --> 41:46.659
(SIRENS WAILING OUTSIDE)

41:55.637 --> 41:57.929
NEWSMAN (ON TV): who nearly
became his roommate,

41:57.939 --> 42:00.406
says he can't fathom the violence.

42:00.416 --> 42:02.801
Gay and lesbian
newspaper society columnist

42:02.811 --> 42:06.871
Nicole Ramirez-Murray says
Cunanan had rich boyfriends

42:06.881 --> 42:10.976
and was a known gigolo,
a man who loved the spotlight.

42:10.986 --> 42:14.420
At Bishop's, a private school
in the affluent La Jolla area,

42:14.430 --> 42:18.149
Cunanan was voted
Most Likely to be Remembered.

42:18.159 --> 42:20.702
Acquaintances and friends
remember Andrew Cunanan

42:20.713 --> 42:24.482
as an affable young man,
not as a serial killer

42:24.493 --> 42:26.677
from the FBI's Ten Most Wanted list.

42:26.688 --> 42:28.554
NEWSMAN: We are live
at the police perimeter,

42:28.565 --> 42:30.457
where they have reinforced all sides.

42:30.468 --> 42:32.335
Now, authorities are hoping
that he is alone

42:32.346 --> 42:34.826
- and that he is looking to surrender.
- (SIRENS WAILING)

42:34.837 --> 42:36.358
LORI: He sees everything.

42:36.369 --> 42:37.945
SCRIMSHAW: He's not coming out.

42:39.840 --> 42:40.897
Cut the power.

42:40.908 --> 42:42.675
- Shields are up...
- (TV CLICKS)

42:48.992 --> 42:50.750
Deploy smoke now. Now.

42:50.760 --> 42:53.061
- (GUNSHOT)
- (GLASS SHATTERS)

42:58.168 --> 43:00.035
(GLASS SHATTERS)

43:01.921 --> 43:03.887
♪ ♪

43:23.093 --> 43:25.060
(GUN RACKS)

43:35.372 --> 43:37.339
♪ ♪

43:40.034 --> 43:42.935
(FOOTSTEPS ECHOING)

43:44.982 --> 43:46.940
ANDREW: <i>I'm so happy right now.</i>

43:46.950 --> 43:48.884
<i>(GUNSHOT)</i>

43:53.023 --> 43:54.909
ANDREW: What if...

43:55.932 --> 44:00.028
you had a dream your whole life
that you were someone special...

44:01.198 --> 44:03.888
but no one believed it?

44:05.520 --> 44:07.754
Not... not really.

44:08.979 --> 44:11.847
They'd smile at you and say,
"Oh, sure, sure."

44:13.110 --> 44:14.693
And then, what if

44:16.060 --> 44:21.483
the first person
that <i> truly</i> believed you...

44:22.651 --> 44:26.243
was the most incredible
person you'd ever met?

44:28.407 --> 44:30.983
But it's not about persuading people

44:30.994 --> 44:33.120
that you're going to do something great.

44:33.130 --> 44:35.440
It's about doing it.

44:36.588 --> 44:38.544
You have to finish your novel.

44:38.555 --> 44:40.688
Or something else.

44:43.974 --> 44:46.300
Do you think I could be a designer?

44:47.650 --> 44:49.169
A designer?

44:49.179 --> 44:53.040
I know literally everything
there is to know about fashion.

44:53.050 --> 44:56.109
Maybe I could assist you
or-or be your protégé?

44:56.119 --> 44:58.111
I'm not looking for an assistant.

44:58.121 --> 45:00.314
But being here...

45:00.932 --> 45:03.527
like this, with-with you, it...

45:06.096 --> 45:08.296
it feels like destiny.

45:12.135 --> 45:14.302
Why can't you feel it?

45:18.342 --> 45:20.942
Andrew. Andrew.

45:26.008 --> 45:28.308
One day you'll understand why I said no.

45:28.318 --> 45:30.210
It's not because
I don't find you attractive.

45:30.220 --> 45:32.012
I invited you here

45:32.022 --> 45:34.414
because you're
a very interesting young man.

45:34.424 --> 45:37.851
I want you to... to be inspired by this,

45:38.284 --> 45:40.449
to be nourished by tonight.

45:41.031 --> 45:43.331
If we kissed...

45:43.861 --> 45:45.661
you may doubt it.

45:46.795 --> 45:48.996
We could go get dinner t...
uh, tomorrow.

45:49.006 --> 45:50.790
I could... I could take you to Stars.

45:50.800 --> 45:53.842
We could talk some more about my novel.

45:53.852 --> 45:55.269
I wish.

45:55.279 --> 45:57.971
But I leave San Francisco soon,
and it's...

45:57.981 --> 45:59.948
There's so much to do.

46:01.985 --> 46:03.952
Another night.

46:05.355 --> 46:07.328
Another stage.

46:08.325 --> 46:10.292
Yes?

46:18.335 --> 46:20.302
♪ ♪

46:26.943 --> 46:28.143
(LIGHTS THUMP)

46:31.214 --> 46:33.204
SCRIMSHAW: <i>Is it him?</i>

46:34.405 --> 46:36.175
LORI: <i>It's him.</i>

46:36.186 --> 46:38.190
What you expected?

46:39.667 --> 46:41.214
He's just a boy.

46:41.224 --> 46:43.291
(SIGHS) Yeah.

46:50.167 --> 46:52.133
- (CAMERAS CLICKING)
- (QUIET CHATTER)

46:57.107 --> 46:59.074
♪ ♪

47:27.250 --> 47:28.868
It's over.

47:30.048 --> 47:32.107
You caught him?

47:32.209 --> 47:34.868
He's dead. He shot himself.

47:36.497 --> 47:38.188
Good.

47:39.691 --> 47:41.204
It's over.

47:47.190 --> 47:48.882
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

47:48.892 --> 47:50.859
TERRY: Marilyn?

47:53.263 --> 47:55.427
Are you okay?

47:57.969 --> 48:01.749
We receive hundreds of letters
each month from viewers.

48:02.672 --> 48:04.945
And since my husband's death,

48:04.955 --> 48:07.275
I started to receive letters about him.

48:08.979 --> 48:10.979
Often from people I-I don't know,

48:10.989 --> 48:13.106
I've never heard of,

48:13.116 --> 48:15.997
whose lives were touched
by Lee in some way.

48:16.008 --> 48:20.582
He-he supported this family when
they got into financial trouble.

48:20.593 --> 48:23.834
He helped this young man's career.

48:24.567 --> 48:28.402
He-he paid their bills
when they couldn't.

48:30.167 --> 48:32.300
And he never...

48:32.402 --> 48:34.545
told me.

48:35.939 --> 48:38.368
About any of it.

48:41.747 --> 48:43.446
Why...

48:44.147 --> 48:46.948
didn't he ever tell me?

48:53.605 --> 48:55.493
I reply to every letter.

48:56.058 --> 49:00.219
I thank them for their
kind words about my husband,

49:00.230 --> 49:01.907
and...

49:03.247 --> 49:08.730
I tell them that he's alive
in their letters...

49:11.274 --> 49:13.308
and that I'm...

49:17.914 --> 49:21.469
so very proud of him.

49:35.873 --> 49:38.841
- (FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)
- WOMAN: Signore.

49:41.679 --> 49:43.645
(QUIET CHATTER)

49:51.990 --> 49:53.922
Donatella.

49:55.960 --> 49:58.036
The lawyers are here.

50:02.575 --> 50:05.767
I have to tell you something.

50:10.390 --> 50:13.609
On the morning Gianni was killed,

50:13.620 --> 50:15.586
he called me.

50:17.503 --> 50:20.117
I was in Rome preparing for that show.

50:21.639 --> 50:24.010
He was up early in Miami,

50:24.021 --> 50:26.670
wanting to know every little detail.

50:28.041 --> 50:31.109
He couldn't just let me do it alone.

50:32.882 --> 50:35.500
When I ended the call, I was annoyed.

50:36.541 --> 50:39.882
I had the show under control.
I didn't need his help.

50:41.502 --> 50:45.707
So, when he called back
30 minutes later...

50:51.882 --> 50:54.583
I didn't answer.

51:00.200 --> 51:02.839
(VOICE BREAKING): I ignored his call.

51:05.563 --> 51:07.888
♪ ♪

